Ensuring that you sleep enough and have good quality sleep should be a student’s “secret weapon” to combat stress, fatigue and anxiety, it signals. Even avoid getting fat, as lack of sleep causes the brain to go into hunger mode, which makes it constantly hungry.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old Californian who studies chemistry and physical biology, helped Professor Czeisler design the course after attending one of his classes last year during his first year at Harvard.
He said the course opened his eyes and inspired him to push a course across campus.
The next step, hopefully, is to ask all postgraduate students to complete a similar study program before joining the competitive institution.
